U.S. had been hacking into computers in China for many years: NSA leaker
2013-06-13 01:50:59 GMT
Whistleblower Edward Snowden who gave details of a secret US National Security Agency program has told a Hong Kong newspaper that the agency had been hacking into computers in Hong Kong and in mainland China, NHK reports.The South China Morning Post in Hong Kong carried an article in its Thursday's edition about its interview with Snowden.The daily reported that Snowden said that there had been more than 61,000 NSA hacking operations throughout the world.Snowden said hacking into computers in Hong Kong and on the mainland China began in 2009. In Hong Kong, he said, it was targeting university and government officials, companies and students.He said he was releasing the information to demonstrate the hypocrisy of the US government.The former NSA contractor said he would stay in Hong Kong and fight the US government in the courts.(Agencies)
